haikus.poem:
Cherry blossoms fall
Softly on the morning dew
Spring awakens now

Moonlight on the lake
Reflects the stars above us
Peaceful night descends

Autumn leaves dancing
In the gentle autumn breeze
Nature's final show

Ocean waves crashing
Against the rocky shoreline
Eternal rhythm

Morning fog lifting
Reveals the mountain's true face
Mystery unfolds

Fireflies at night
Dancing in the summer air
Nature's lanterns glow

Winter's first snowfall
Blankets the sleeping garden
Silent transformation

Bamboo forest path
Leads to ancient temple grounds
Time stands still here

Morning coffee steam
Rises in the early light
Day begins anew

Desert wind whispers
Through the ancient canyon walls
Echoes of time past

Rainbow after rain
Bridges earth and sky above
Hope's gentle promise

Mountain stream flowing
Over moss-covered stones
Nature's melody

Sunset colors paint
The evening sky with wonder
Day bids farewell now

Garden spider spins
Her web in morning sunlight
Art in nature's hands

Thunder in the night
Lightning flashes through the clouds
Storm's wild symphony

Maple leaves turning
From green to gold and crimson
Autumn's masterpiece

Morning dew drops shine
Like diamonds in the grass
Nature's jewelry

Bees in the garden
Dancing from flower to flower
Spring's busy workers

Northern lights dance
Across the Arctic night sky
Aurora's ballet

Desert cactus blooms
In the harsh midday sunlight
Beauty in extremes

Morning mist rising
Over the valley below
Day's gentle birth

Ocean tide rising
Brings treasures to the shore
Nature's gifts arrive

Mountain peak piercing
Through the clouds above
Earth touches the sky

Frost on window glass
Creating crystal patterns
Winter's artwork

Cherry tree blossoms
Falling in the springtime breeze
Pink snow in the air
